dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag run out (Perera) 96 (97b 10x4 0x6 132m) SR: 98.96

dismissalComment.html: Run-out, Sehwag is walking back, better from Thisara, he held back his length this time a touch while bowling it straight, Kohli dropped it into the off side, Sehwag wanted the single and had taken a start but Kohli sent him back, Thisara collected and did superbly to throw down the stumps at the non-striker's end to catch Sehwag short. He's missed his century

headshotImage.longCaption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: back to over the wicket for Umesh, sliced over the extra-cover fielder, they didn't go for the single, India have won

commentPostTextItems.html: Sri Lanka would have had India a little unsettled when Perera and Sangakkara were going strong, but the asking rate was climbing consistently. Under those circumstances, with only one partnership giving them a realistic shot, India were favourites. Dilshan fell early and Sangakkara and Tharanga couldn't really push on given the asking rate. Sanga got a century, but the acceleration should have come much earlier than it did. India will be happy with the win, coming after a longish break. Abhishek Purohit's match report should be getting updated. I'll join you at the presentation.
Time for the presentation after a longish break. There are several awards including one for the partnership of the match etc. Virat Kohli is Man of the Match for his century.

Kohli: "God's been kind, I've been working hard. Hopefully I can be consistent for the team this season. Performing for my country is the biggest thing for me, and I try to give my best out there for the team. Doing well in Australia really boosted my confidence, and that Test hundred really helped."

Jayawardene: "We've got some big-hitters at the end, but we left too much for them to do. Too many mistakes, against a quality side like India. It was important for us to set up a platform, Sanga was trying to build an innings. We never had momentum going into the last 10 overs. We'll try to refocus and come back strong. Kulasekara and Lasith are two big guys I rely on during the Powerplays, but we need to improve our standards in the field."

Dhoni: "The death bowling for us needs to improve. Zak was good, one good positive was Irfan Pathan doing well. Without Jadeja or Yuvraj, it is difficult to make a side balanced in both departments so this was important. It's a good learning experience for the younger bowlers. Gautam was unfortunate to get out in that fashion. Sehwag and Kohli batted very well, we are lacking a bit of firepower down the line. Once the batsmen who are set carry on, then me, and the likes of Raina can go and express ourselves. This was one game where I felt the toss would be crucial. In the second innings, there was variable bounce and it was a little difficult to bat on."
That's it, folks. At The Oval, South Africa are in the ascendancy. Join us again on the 24th for the next match, to be held at the same venue. See you then. Thanks, and goodbye.

commentPreTextItems.html: Irfan has finished a good comeback spell, Umesh to finish the game now

commentPreTextItems.html: 46 needed off three, Umesh runs in

commentTextItems.html: got him, he's bowled him, Sanga moved well across to scoop that fine but missed, that was aimed at leg stump from round the wicket and that's where it was heading when Sanga failed to make contact

commentPostTextItems.html: He walks back with 133 to his name but could he have stepped up much earlier than he did? His innings slowed down considerably at one stage. Kulasekara's not in, his injury has prevented him from coming out at No.9. It's Herath who walks in

commentTextItems.html: Too quick for Dhoni, pitched up and Perera went after that one too, got a thick edge and past a diving MS Dhoni who leapt to his left but could not get his hands to it, flew past him for a boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: India would have loved that wicket, but just seven came off that over.

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag run out (Perera) 96 (97b 10x4 0x6 132m) SR: 98.96

dismissalComment.html: Run-out, Sehwag is walking back, better from Thisara, he held back his length this time a touch while bowling it straight, Kohli dropped it into the off side, Sehwag wanted the single and had taken a start but Kohli sent him back, Thisara collected and did superbly to throw down the stumps at the non-striker's end to catch Sehwag short. He's missed his century

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma b Mathews 5 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: Angelo's struck, two wickets in quick time, did that nip back in? Short of a good length, landed on the off and appeared to just nip back in, Rohit was late on it and was eventually beaten through the gate, it knocked back off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c sub (SMSM Senanayake) b Perera 106 (113b 9x4 0x6 158m) SR: 93.8

dismissalComment.html: Kohli has to go, a sharp catch at extra cover, was the slower one, Kohli picked it and struck it well, but he was looking to clear extra cover there but couldn't get the elevation, Sachitra Senanayake, the substitute fielder, presumably for Kulasekara, stayed alert and snapped it well

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c sub (SMSM Senanayake) b Perera 50 (45b 3x4 1x6 75m) SR: 111.11

dismissalComment.html: a meaty full toss but Raina can't cash in this time, swings hard, gets the top edge and Senanayake, the substitute, who's already taken one good catch this innings, makes no mistake. He was at square leg and he turned, ran a few steps and judged it to perfection

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni c Thirimanne b Perera 35 (29b 3x4 1x6 49m) SR: 120.68

dismissalComment.html: he's played that shot well this innings and he struck that one hard too, but the whiplash fails to clear long-off this time, Thirimanne, standing there, moves back a few steps and takes it over his head

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c Sehwag b Ashwin 28 (47b 2x4 0x6 87m) SR: 59.57

dismissalComment.html: short and wide and after four dot balls, Tharanga looks for a release off a short delivery with some width, tries to slash it through point, gets a thick edge and it ricocheted off Dhoni's glove towards first slip

headshotImage.caption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Irfan Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan lbw b Pathan 6 (6b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: appeal for lbw and the umpire has given it out! That one swung in to the right-hander as well, landed on middle and leg and appeared to strike him in line as he tried to whip that off the back foot, would it have gone over? And did he get an inside edge? Umpire Oxenford's finger went up fairly quickly. We need to have another look, but Sehwag's lapse doesn't cost India much

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara b Yadav 133 (151b 12x4 0x6 208m) SR: 88.07

dismissalComment.html: got him, he's bowled him, Sanga moved well across to scoop that fine but missed, that was aimed at leg stump from round the wicket and that's where it was heading when Sanga failed to make contact

headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c Dhoni b Yadav 13 (19b 1x4 0x6 25m) SR: 68.42

dismissalComment.html: Chandimal has to go, short of a good length and a bit of away movement, Chandimal fishes for that one, gets a thin edge and is snapped up by Dhoni

headshotImage.caption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene lbw b Ojha 12 (8b 1x4 0x6 13m) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: trapped in front is Mahela! Angling in from round the wicket and it held its line, Mahela had made his mind up to play the paddle-sweep, struck him in line, but we need another replay to see if that would have gone on to hit the stumps, the umpire thought so and Sri Lanka are in trouble now

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Gambhir b Khan 7 (17b 0x4 0x6 31m) SR: 41.17

dismissalComment.html: Mathews has been caught at cover and Sri Lanka have lost another one, made room, had made up his mind there, short of a good length and his intention was to clear the field on the off-side, mistimed it and spooned an easy catch to Gambhir, appeared to be a slower one from Zaheer

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne lbw b Ashwin 7 (10b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: given out lbw, the carrom ball, that spun in towards Lahiru, Ashwin was bowling round the wicket, Lahiru went across to work it into the leg side, missed and was caught on the pads. The umpire Martinez gave it out immediately, though the question is whether or not it would have missed leg. We'll need another replay for that. Meanwhile, Lahiru has to go

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera c Kohli b Pathan 44 (28b 3x4 1x6 52m) SR: 157.14

dismissalComment.html: holes out, that pitched on a length and he smashed it straight but didn't get hold of it, found Virat Kohli at long-on, Perera walks back, though we may just have Kula walk in

dismissalText.commentary: Rangana Herath run out (Raina) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: low full toss and that's been drilled towards long-off, Raina collects and scores a direct hit from the deep to catch Herath short as he attempts a second, Umesh did it smartly there, didn't collect the throw, allowed it to roll onto the stumps, Herath is run-out

dismissalText.commentary: Lasith Malinga not out 19 (10b 1x4 2x6 14m) SR: 190
